# Knowledge Vault — Agent Instructions

This vault stores research, decisions, and session logs for all projects.
It is separate from code repos. Agents read it for context; they never push to
a code remote from here.

## Vault Structure

| Folder | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `Projects/{name}/` | Per-project research, notes, decisions, session logs |
| `Projects/{name}/_context.md` | LLM entry point for that project (L1) |
| `Projects/{name}/Research/` | Source-extracted research docs |
| `Projects/{name}/sessions/` | SESSION_LOG.md + archive |
| `Knowledge/` | Cross-project insights and extracts |
| `Knowledge/patterns/` | Reusable patterns with context/pattern/why structure |
| `_inbox/` | Zero-friction capture. Process with `/process-inbox` |
| `_meta/` | Vault conventions, this file, indexes |

## Context Loading Protocol (L0 → L1 → L2)

| Level | File | When to read |
|-------|------|-------------|
| L0 | `NEXT.md` in the code repo | Every session — what to work on |
| L1 | `Projects/{name}/_context.md` | Every session — project summary and doc index |
| L2 | Full docs in `Projects/{name}/Research/` or `docs/` | Only when L1 indicates relevance |

**Rule:** Never read L2 docs unless the L1 summary or current task explicitly
requires them. This keeps token usage predictable.

## Knowledge Location Rules

| Belongs in vault | Belongs in repo |
|-----------------|-----------------|
| Research notes and extracts | Source code |
| Session logs | NEXT.md (session continuity) |
| Decision rationale and history | docs/_context/DECISIONS.md (decision log) |
| Cross-project patterns | docs/_context/BRIEF.md (project overview) |
| Long-form notes | README, inline comments |

When in doubt: **repo for operational, vault for knowledge.**

## Frontmatter Requirements

Every file must include the fields defined in `_meta/conventions.md`.
Required fields: `title`, `type`, `project`, `tags`, `created`, `updated`,
`status`, `confidence`, `language`, `summary`.

See `_meta/conventions.md` for allowed values and naming rules.

## Inbox Rule

Drop raw captures into `_inbox/`. Never route them manually.
Run `/process-inbox` to classify, add frontmatter, and place them correctly.
